76561198047954782,Recommended,221020,7788044,"Posted: 27 November, 2013",all,Hero-of-Canton,"This is a fun little town simulation game with challenging gameplay and lots of facets to it.  I have definitely enjoyed it, despite the fact that I have gotten stuck numerous times trying to figure out how to progress which leads me to the game's problems.  This is still in development, and it shows.  A lot of aspects aren't explained very well and a lot of things about your villagers are hard to control.  For example, to get more villagers your villagers need to be happy.  Happiness is influenced by numerous factors, how nice their rooms are, what variety of things they have to eat, what kind of decorations they have to look at but also how much work they have to do.  If they have too much work they get stressed but if they have too little they get bored, there's no way to tell villagers how much of their time to spend relaxing and how much working (aside from a somewhat unpredictable job assignment system).  There is a great community forum with a lot of mods for the game and that helps but I cant help but wish they had more streamlining.Pros:Neat ConceptGood MechanicsTons of replayability (due to procedural generation)Fun and not overcomplicated simCons:Less-than-optimal controlsPoor in-game instructions"
