76561198114555138,Recommended,221020,7733548,"Posted: 24 November, 2013",all,BoarWarrior,"It's nice after you get into it. No proper tutorial makes a bit hard in the beginning, but no deal-breaker. This isn't the short 2-hour game, you can really spend time there, it's a crude version of Sims combined with Minecraft in strategy mode where you command a lot of ""minecraft players"", your citizens. The commands are leaned towards automation so you dont have so much direct control, but enough for sure.Note: this game was supposedly made by one programmer and one artist and the programmer has allegedly quit this project (and there's rumors this project was never a high priority thing for him) so dont expect the bugs to be fixed. I did enjoy the game, but that's because I like to discover new things, even find out the game mechanics instead of having them explained to me. Anyone who feels differently, you shouldn't buy this game because there's a lot finding-out to do with game mechanics, and that's most likely not gonna change.The game mechanics work though, it's just a long try & fail process often. But you can also make up for your failures, like build new if buildings get destroyed (they shouldn't), get new villagers if old ones die (how compassionate) and even buy new animals from the visiting vendors.I feel this game has a lot of potential, but is poorly polished. I dont know how much the developers make with this, but they could make 10 times more bucks if they polished it, hired the crew and decided to listen to people."
