,Recommended,221020,11675557,"Posted: 12 August, 2014",all,Neo,"Though this game may be dead, and it may not be worth $15, but I still paid for it and haven't regretted the investment since... well, as far as the gameplay is concerned; I regret funding a dev team that couldn't finish their Early Access game, but as far as how the game plays in its final state, it's still fun enough. Setting up a thriving town in this game is a real uphill battle, with so many things that can go wrong and things that can just tear your barely-surviving town apart. When you get new settlers to arrive at the map borders, it's also a challenge to make sure they can get to town safely. However, the more you fight and the more you work, the stronger your villagers will become, and the better they can survive in the harsh wilderness. It's a real satisfying feeling to beat the odds and set up a thriving community in this game... and then the seiges and the werepigs come in and wreck your day...If you can pick this game up for about $5 or less during a sale or something (or you preferrably have ways to get it for free), I'd say it's worth looking into. Nothing mind-blowing, but a decent time-waster nonetheless."
