,Recommended,221020,19316296,"Posted: 27 November, 2015",all,Ethertrauma,"I am not one to write lengthy, detailed reviews, but I must say that this game is definitely misunderstood by many.If you are looking for a game in which every detail is given to you, where there is nothing to be learned and no difficulty in creating things, then continue no further.If you are someone who likes unique, one of a kind games that contain many interesting elements native to that game alone, then I do suggest Towns. It is a somewhat addicting city-builder with both rpg and survival aspects. Building is complicated at first, even for simulation and survival vets like myself. Even after the horribly furstrating first attempts at creating a town, I find myself coming back. It's definitely a challenge at first, but as you slowly get a grip on the isometric perspective and somewhat aggravating UI, you begin to discover new things and gain new knowledge, and that is part of what makes this game so golden.The game isn't broken, it is justdifficultat first. It definitely is not for everyone, but if you want a unique, expansive, and nostalgic city-builder, please buy this game. You will not regret it."
