76561198047977817,Recommended,221020,35207041,Posted: 25 September,all,Sogreth,"I'll start off with...I love this game! I've had many hours of fun with it. Many different things to still try, lots of things to build and explore. I'm still in the middle of building a massive castle! I haven't found anything wrong with the game so far. No gamebreaking bugs, or anything along those lines. And it's a fun game to play.I have heard rumors that the game was been ""abandoned"", and is ""unfinished"". But I don't think a game like this needs constant updates anyways, and I don't really feel like it's unfinished. It's not like an RPG game that has a difinitive ending, you can literaly do anything you want. Just look at some of the screenshots!The one thing I had problems with was digging into the ground to open up the Dungeon. Sometimes I just end up making a mess, and it can be hard to block it off (if you don't monsters can come up and attack your town), but other than that, I haven't had any real issues with the game.In the end, if you like building things from scratch or making an arsenal of weapons and armor for the ""Heroes"" to use to clear out the dungeons, then you'll like this game. It's worth the money."
,Recommended,221020,35239599,Posted: 27 September,all,HAL-9000,"Personally, I still really enjoy this game for what it is and not what people are trying to make it be. If I feel like I can idly do something I usually hit up Towns if I'm in the mood. I really enjoy making a trading town that just constantly makes money every time a trader comes and making a defense line that just about nothing can break through. There is a learning curve but its pretty easy once you realize how to get things together. People screech that the dev has abandonded the game but I could care less since I already enjoy it for what it is instead of whining of what could be."
